special_powers.name: WEB-PUNCH
special_powers.description: Spider-Man can use Flurry. If he makes two successful attacks against the same target using Flurry, instead of dealing damage with the second attack he can instead give an action token to the target if it has zero or one action token.

special_powers.name: TENTACLES
special_powers.description: Dr. Octopus can use Flurry, Leap/Climb, and Super Strength.

special_powers.name: EXTREMIS
special_powers.description: Iron Man can use Outwit and Perplex. When a power or ability is not countered by Iron Man's Outwit, he can use Super Senses.

special_powers.name: GOOD FORTUNE THUNDER KICK
special_powers.description: Iron Fist can use Leap/Climb and Flurry.

special_powers.name: CHAMPION OF K'UN-LUN
special_powers.description: Iron Fist can use Super Senses and Willpower.

special_powers.name: CHAINGUN
special_powers.description: Once per turn when the Punisher succeeds at a ranged combat attack against an opposing target character, after the attack resolves he can immediately make ranged combat attacks against any other opposing characters adjacent to the target to which he can draw a clear line of fire. (Each attack is rolled and deals damage separately). If the result of a successful ranged combat attack roll made by the Punisher is doubles, the damage dealt is penetrating damage.

special_powers.name: PLIABLE
special_powers.description: Mr. Fantastic can use Leap/Climb and Plasticity

special_powers.name: DUCTILE
special_powers.description: Mr. Fantastic can use Super Senses and Barrier (as if he had a range of 0). When a Barrier terrain marker placed by Mr. Fantastic is destroyed, roll a d6; on a result of 1, deal 1 damage to Mr. Fantastic.

special_powers.name: INVENTIVE GENIUS
special_powers.description: Mr. Fantastic can use Perplex, but he can modify the target's combat values by +2 or -2 if he is targeting himself of another character with which he shares a keyword.

special_powers.name: INVISIBLE
special_powers.description: Any character that is 7 or more squares from the Invisible Woman can't draw a line of fire to her.

special_powers.name: FORCE FIELDS
special_powers.description: Invisible Woman can use Barrier and Invulnerability.

special_powers.name: NONE SHALL INTERFERE WITH THE PLANS OF DOOM
special_powers.description: Dr. Doom can use Running Shot.  Dr. Doom breaks away automatically.

special_powers.name: KNEEL BEFORE DOOM!
special_powers.description: Dr. Doom can use Energy Explosion, but deals damage equal to his damage value to the target of the attack. Characters adjacent to the target are dealt damage normally.

special_powers.name: ARMORED MASTERMIND
special_powers.description: Dr. Doom can use Invulnerability and Mastermind.

special_powers.name: LORD OF LATVERIA
special_powers.description: Dr. Doom can use Outwit and Perplex. When Dr. Doom uses Outwit, he can use it normally, or you can roll a d6 instead; on a result of 4-6, counter a power possessed by a single target opposing character anywhere on the battlefield.

special_powers.name: FIERY STREAK
special_powers.description: Human Torch can use Running Shot. When he does not use the Carry ability while moving, Human Torch does not have to end his movement if he enters a square adjacent to an opposing character.

special_powers.name: FLAME ON!
special_powers.description: Human Torch can use Energy Shield/Deflection and Poison. When Human Torch is given a move action or power action, immediately after resolving the action, he can use Smoke Cloud as a free action, but can place hindering terrain only in squares he moved through or occupied this turn.

special_powers.name: IT'S CLOBBERIN' TIME
special_powers.description: The Thing can use Quake. Give the Thing a power action; he can move up to his speed value and then as a free action either (1) use Quake or (2) make a close combat attack.

special_powers.name: YANCY STREETER
special_powers.description: The Thing can use Toughness and Willpower.

special_powers.name: YER EVER-LOVIN' PAL
special_powers.description: At the beginning of your turn, if the Thing is adjacent to one or more friendly characters that have one or more action tokens, roll a d6. On a result of 5 or 6, you can remove an action token from one adjacent friendly character, or two adjacent friendly characters if they and the Thing all possess a single common keyword.

special_powers.name: LORD OF THE TUNNELS
special_powers.description: Mole Man can use Stealth and Phasing/Teleport. When Mole Man uses Phasing/Teleport, he can use the Carry ability and must put debris tokens into the squares where he begins and ends his move. Mole Man ignores the effects of debris tokens on movement.

special_powers.name: FULL POWER
special_powers.description: When Iron Man is given a ranged combat action targeting a single character, roll one d6 if the attack succeeds. The result replaces Iron Man's damage value for the attack. After the attack is resolved, Iron Man is dealt 2 unavoidable damage.
